20. CloudWatch

Service that allows you to monitor various elements of your AWS account. Resources and applications are monitored in real time.
Collect and track metrics, sends alarms, or make changes based on rules that a user defines.

Can create custom widgets to make it more convenient to look at metrics.

Alarms can perform automated actions based on certain conditions and metrics a user makes.

Cloudwatch Benefits:
Monitor metrics for almost all of your AWS Resources
Create and monitor custom metrics
Create custom dashboards for easy viewing of metrics
Set alarms and events


However, CloudWatch doesn't monitor user events.

--------------------------------
21. CloudTrail

Allows you to monitor all actions taken by IAM users. (like logging who deleted an S3 object)
Service that enables governance, compliance, operational auditing, and risk auditing of AWS account.
